<subSubSection id="49C942EEFF883950EBD2C68CFB085904" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" type="diagnosis">
<paragraph id="016C1165FF883950EBD2C68CFEA35AEF" blockId="38.[227,348,447,473]" box="[227,348,447,473]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">
<heading id="5A24A609FF883950EBD2C68CFEA35AEF" bold="true" box="[227,348,447,473]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="38" pageNumber="39" reason="3">
<emphasis id="33A7CD77FF883950EBD2C68CFEA35AEF" bold="true" box="[227,348,447,473]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">Diagnosis</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="016C1165FF883950EBD2C6C2FB085904" blockId="38.[227,1436,497,562]" pageId="38" pageNumber="39">OL/OH = 1.17–1.25. Elliptic otoliths with protruding dorsal area in the middle. Sulcus wide, long, but not divided into ostium and cauda. Narrow ostial channel present at antero-dorsal corner.</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
